Lab: Configure Authentication and Authorization
Configure the HTPasswd identity provider, create groups, and assign roles to users and groups.
Outcomes
Create users and passwords for HTPasswd authentication.
Configure the identity provider for HTPasswd authentication.
Assign cluster administration rights to users.
Remove the ability to create projects at the cluster level.
Create groups and add users to groups.
Manage user privileges in projects by granting privileges to groups

1. Core Concepts (Very Important)
Authentication
Authentication answers:
Who are you?
Examples:
•	LDAP
•	HTPasswd
•	GitHub OAuth
•	Google OAuth
•	Keystone
In this lab we use:
HTPasswd Identity Provider
This means usernames/passwords are stored in a file like:
username:hashedpassword
________________________________________
Authorization (RBAC)
Authorization answers:
What are you allowed to do?
OpenShift uses RBAC (Role-Based Access Control).
Example:
Role	Permission
cluster-admin	full cluster control
admin	project administration
edit	modify resources
view	read-only
________________________________________
